    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>INTEREST RATE UNCHANGED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bank of England leaves its benchmark interest rate unchanged at 6 percent for seventh consecutive month; inflation in July was at annualized 2.2 percent, below government's target of 2.5 percent; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>With signs that economic growth is easing, the Bank of England left its benchmark interest rate unchanged at 6 percent for the seventh consecutive month. The decision had little impact on foreign exchange markets, where the British pound has slipped by 6 percent against the dollar in the last three months. The bank's decision coincided with data suggesting that car sales are falling and both retail prices and wage increases are slowing. The combination left inflation in July at an annualized 2.2 percent, below the government's target of 2.5 percent.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
